msgid "**Updates**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:50
msgid ":command:`lumina-calculator`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:52
msgid ""
"Clean up precision of reported results and how they are re-used for later "
"calculations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:54
msgid "Added ability to clear or save history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:55
msgid ""
"Tag each result with \"#X\" and allow that shortcut to be used in an "
"equation to recall the result of that calculation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:57
msgid ""
"Add tons of scientific functionality to the calculator without bloating the "
"interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:60
msgid ":command:`lumina-config`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:62
msgid ""
"Clean up the main page considerably: 2 columns, auto-expanded items, and "
"more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:64
msgid ""
"In the main page, add the ability to change the current Qt5 theme engine for"
" external applications."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:66
msgid ""
"Add entries for newer desktop backend systems (compositor start/skip "
"detection, new plugins, etc)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:68
msgid ""
"Add a new page for managing Xorg input device properties (requires "
"*xinput*)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:70
msgid ""
"Add pre-defined *profiles* to the interface/panels page. Available options: "
"*No panels*, *Windows*, *GNOME2/MATE*, *XFCE*, and *Mac OSX*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:73
msgid ""
"Add the ability to *import* panel configuration settings from one monitor to"
" another, even if the original monitor is not currently enabled or active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:77
msgid ":command:`lumina-desktop`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:79
msgid ""
"Fix up some wallpaper update issues with monitor resizes and Fluxbox "
"eccentricity."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:81
msgid ""
"Add right-click passthrough to many desktop plugins so the overall *plugin* "
"menu functions no matter where the click happens on the plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:84
msgid ""
"Fix up the panel *autohide* functionality to it will work on screen edges "
"*between* monitors as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:86
msgid ""
"Speed up the initial start of the desktop, but delay the auto-started "
"applications by 1/2 second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:88
msgid "Clean up some mimetype detection routines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:89
msgid ""
"Clean up some more systems to ensure they use the monitor ID for loading or "
"saving desktop settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:91
msgid ""
"Add a green background to the battery notifiers if the battery is fully "
"charged, but still plugged in."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:93
msgid ""
"Make the *start menu* open faster by only re-loading the favorites when they"
" change."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:95
msgid ""
"Make the *applauncher* panel plugin able to auto-complete the path to "
":file:`*.desktop` files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:97
msgid ""
"Make the *clock* panel plugin auto-adjust the number of lines of text to "
"show depending on the panel size/orientation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:99
msgid "Adjust the margins in the menus to work better on 4K monitors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:100
msgid "Clean up some vertical-panel plugin behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:101
msgid ""
"Clean up the boot splash when starting the desktop. Now it displays the "
"version of the desktop and some random *message of the day*, in addition to "
"the normal loading indicators."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:105
msgid ""
"The *message of the day* (motd) can be changed by creating a :file:`lumina-"
"motd` file and placing it into :file:`<LOCALBASE>/etc` alongside "
":file:`luminaDesktop.conf`. If the new file is executable, Lumina will run "
"the file and print any text that is output. Otherwise, it will read and "
"display contents of the file as plaintext. For example, a blank file will "
"disable the motd."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:112
msgid ":command:`lumina-fm`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:114
msgid ""
"Fix up some issues with directory modifications through the right column of "
"a split view."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:116
msgid ""
"Fix up the re-loading of the *show hidden files* option when starting new "
"viewers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:118
msgid ""
"Re-enable drag and drop functionality (missed that with the latest overhaul "
"to the viewers)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:120
msgid ""
"Fix an issue with symlinks in the path preventing the ZFS snapshot finder "
"from working properly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:123
msgid ""
":command:`lumina-open`: Update the crash monitor to only trigger when the "
"process actually crashes by disabling the return code checking (some apps "
"intentionally return non-zero and were getting flagged as crashes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:128
msgid ":command:`lumina-screenshot`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:130
msgid ""
"Add better error reporting when a screenshot can not save for some reason."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:132
msgid "Cleanup the scaling rules for the *zoom* functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:134
msgid ":command:`lumina-search`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:136
msgid "Apply more limits to the background search process handling."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:137
msgid ""
"Avoid trawling through the :file:`proc` directory heirarchy at all costs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:139
msgid "Bump the time to start the live search from 1/3 to 1/2 second."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:141
msgid ":command:`start-lumina-desktop`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:143
msgid ""
"Modify the Qt5/dbus crash workaround to avoid starting up a dbus session if "
"at all possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:145
msgid "Checked and cleaned up any :command:`lumina-desktop` lockfiles."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:147
msgid "FreeBSD: Add PulseAudio support for TrueOS PICO sessions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:689
msgid ""
"Add support to |lumina| :ref:`Screenshot` for multi-screen arrangements and "
"for including and excluding window borders for single window snapshots."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:741
msgid ""
"Completely overhaul the :ref:`File Information` utility. Now it is an almost"
" complete front-end for the Qt/Lumina file information and XDG entry "
"structures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:748
msgid ""
"Decrease initial loading time of |lumina| :ref:`Configuration` by making it "
"load all the background image thumbnails on demand instead of up-front."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:755
msgid ""
"Update the application selection in the fileopen dialog of |lumina| "
":ref:`Open`, making it much easier to find the proper application to open "
"the specified file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:790
msgid "Update URL syntax handling in |lumina| :ref:`Open`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:804
msgid ""
"Add a small CLI flag to |lumina| :ref:`Open` for testing the crash handler "
"(\"-testcrash\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:900
msgid ""
"There is a known conflict between Qt 5.4+ and Fluxbox 1.3.7 which prevents "
"the “close” button from working on unlocked desktop plugins. To work around "
"this issue, right-click on the title for the plugin and select the “close” "
"option from the menu to remove the desktop plugin. Alternatively, you may "
"also remove desktop plugins using the :ref:`Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:994
msgid ""
"Add |lumina| :ref:`Xconfig`, a graphical front-end to :command:`xrandr`. "
"This utility can be used to easily enable or disable additional monitors and"
" screens within the current desktop session. Shortcuts to this utility are "
"available in the user button plugin and the settings menu plugin."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1119
msgid ""
"New backend distribution framework for setting system-wide defaults. This "
"affects new users only as existing settings will not be changed. Also added "
"the ability to reset the desktop back to its defaults using the "
":ref:`Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1140
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in |lumina| :ref:`Open` for filenames containing multiple \".\"s"
" not detecting the file extension."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1160
msgid "Better crash reporting through |lumina| :ref:`Open`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1196
msgid ""
"New backend system for registering default applications using mime-types "
"instead of extensions. While all Lumina utilities have been updated to work "
"with the new system, previously registered defaults might not be "
"transferred. You may need to reset your default web browser and email client"
" using the :ref:`Configuration` utility."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1240
msgid ""
"Add |lumina| :ref:`Screenshot`, a simple utility to create and save "
"screenshots. It can capture the entire system or individual windows. It can "
"delay the image capture for a few seconds as necessary. This utility is "
"automatically assigned to the “Print Screen” keyboard shortcut and is also "
"listed in the application registry under \"utilities\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1247
msgid ""
"Add a new implementation of the :ref:`Configuration` utility. It can now be "
"used to configure desktop appearance such as the background image and to add"
" desktop plugins, configure the location, color, transparency, and size of "
"panels as well as manage their plugins, with up to two panels supported per "
"screen, configure menu plugins, manage global keyboard shortcuts, including "
"shortcuts for adjusting audio volume or screen brightness, manage default "
"applications for the system by categories or individually, manage session "
"options such as enable numlock on log in or to play audio chimes, manage "
"applications and files to be launched on log in, and to manage window system"
" options such as appearance, mouse focus policy, window placement policy, "
"and the number of workspaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../changelog.rst:1260
msgid ""
"Update the overall appearance of the application selector window in |lumina|"
" :ref:`Open`."
msgstr ""

